  "local_port": 49490,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I get 95%+ in Class 12th Boards? What reference books can I use for it?",
  "response": "Achieving **95% or above in Class 12th Boards** requires **consistent effort, smart planning, and effective strategies**. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you score high, along with **recommended reference books** for each subject:\n\n---\n\n### **Step 1: Understand the Syllabus and Exam Pattern**\n- Thoroughly go through the **official syllabus** and **weightage of chapters** for each subject.\n- Familiarize yourself with the **exam pattern**, marking scheme, and question distribution.\n\n---\n\n### **Step 2: Create a Study Plan**\n- Divide your time equally among all subjects, focusing more on weaker areas.\n- Allocate specific time slots for **revision**, **practice**, and **mock tests**.\n- Follow a **timetable** to ensure discipline and consistency.\n\n---\n\n### **Step 3: Master NCERT Textbooks**\n- **NCERT books** are the **most important** resource for Class 12 Boards.\n- Read every chapter thoroughly and solve all **NCERT exercises**, examples, and back questions.\n- For subjects like Science and Maths, **NCERT is the foundation**.\n\n---\n\n### **Step 4: Use Subject-Specific Reference Books**\nHere are some **recommended books** for each subject:\n\n#### **Mathematics**:\n  - NCERT Textbook\n  - **RD Sharma** for additional practice\n  - **RS Aggarwal** for problem-solving\n  - **Arihant\u2019s Exemplar Problems** for advanced questions\n\n#### **Physics**:\n  - NCERT Textbook\n  - **Concepts of Physics by HC Verma** (Vol 1 and Vol 2)\n  - **Dinesh Companion** for numerical practice\n  - **Pradeep\u2019s Physics** for conceptual clarity\n\n#### **Chemistry**:\n  - NCERT Textbook\n  - **Physical Chemistry by OP Tandon**\n  - **Organic Chemistry by Morrison and Boyd**\n  - **Modern\u2019s ABC of Chemistry** for additional practice\n  - **Pradeep\u2019s Chemistry** for in-depth understanding\n\n#### **Biology**:\n  - NCERT Textbook\n  - **Pradeep\u2019s Biology** for detailed explanations\n  - **Trueman\u2019s Biology** for diagrams and theory\n  - **NCERT Exemplar** for practice\n\n#### **Accountancy**:\n  - NCERT Textbook\n  - **TS Grewal** for practical problems\n  - **DK Goel** for additional practice\n\n#### **Economics**:\n  - NCERT Textbook\n  - **Sandeeep Garg** (Micro and Macro Economics)\n  - **TR Jain and VK Ohri** for additional questions\n\n#### **Business Studies**:\n  - NCERT Textbook\n  - **Poonam Gandhi** for case studies and practice questions\n\n#### **English**:\n  - NCERT Textbook for literature\n  - **Wren & Martin** for grammar\n  - Practice sample papers for writing skills\n\n---\n\n### **Step 5: Practice Previous Years\u2019 Papers**\n- Solve **at least 5\u201310 years\u2019 past papers** to understand the pattern and frequently asked questions.\n- Analyze your mistakes and work on improving them.\n\n---\n\n### **Step 6: Focus on Time Management**\n- Practice solving papers within the allotted time to improve speed and accuracy.\n- Divide your time wisely during exams to attempt all questions.\n\n---\n\n### **Step 7: Revise Regularly**\n- Revise **NCERT notes**, formulas, and key concepts regularly.\n- Create **short notes** or flashcards for quick revision.\n\n---\n\n### **Step 8: Stay Healthy and Positive**\n- Maintain a **healthy routine** with proper sleep, exercise, and diet.\n- Avoid stress and stay confident in your preparation.\n\n---\n\n### Additional Tips:\n- Use **YouTube channels** like Unacademy, Vedantu, or Khan Academy for difficult topics.\n- Join **online test series** to evaluate your preparation.\n- Discuss doubts with teachers or peers regularly.\n\n---\n\nBy following these strategies and using the suggested resources, you can maximize your chances of scoring **95%+ in Class 12th Boards**. All the best! \ud83d\ude0a",
  "temperature": 1.0,
